---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Grow in Wisdom — Weekly Character Plan"
  description="Deep dive: a full 8-trait weekly character formation plan built around Loving, Humble, Self-Controlled, Hopeful, Wise, Joyful, Peaceful, and Courageous — each with a four-step reflection framework."
  canonicalPath="/grow-in-wisdom/takeaways-character-plan/"
>
  <div class="takeaways-content cp-page">
    <span class="takeaways-tag">Grow in Wisdom</span>
    <h1 class="takeaways-title">Weekly Character Plan</h1>
    <p class="cp-subtitle">God's will for your life is to be conformed to the image of His Son.</p>

    <div class="cp-grid">

      <article class="cp-card" id="trait-loving">
        <div class="cp-card-top">
          <h2 class="cp-trait">Loving</h2>
          <p class="cp-descriptors">Unconditional · Sacrificial · Forgiving</p>
          <div class="cp-framework-name">The Love Audit</div>
        </div>
        <p class="cp-recall">Recall one interaction where love was tested.</p>
        <div class="cp-steps">
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Examine</span>
            <p>What did I want that I wasn't getting? What story am I telling myself?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Reorient</span>
            <p>What burden might they be carrying? When have I needed grace like this?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Release</span>
            <p>Write a forgiveness statement towards this person. What is one concrete way I can express unconditional love through this situation or in the next one?</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cp-remember">
          <span class="cp-remember-label">Remember</span>
          Love is seeing the person, not just the problem.
        </div>
        <div class="cp-scripture">"Love one another as I have loved you." — Jn. 13:34</div>
      </article>

      <article class="cp-card" id="trait-humble">
        <div class="cp-card-top">
          <h2 class="cp-trait">Humble</h2>
          <p class="cp-descriptors">Accountable · Teachable · Selfless</p>
          <div class="cp-framework-name">The Mirror &amp; Window</div>
        </div>
        <p class="cp-recall">Recall a moment you felt superior, defensive, or needed to be right.</p>
        <div class="cp-steps">
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Mirror (Inward)</span>
            <p>What was I protecting or promoting about myself? What weakness or limitation am I reluctant to admit?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Window (Outward)</span>
            <p>Who did I overlook, interrupt, or dismiss—and where did pride keep me from listening or asking for help? How would this situation have changed if I had led with humility?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Ground</span>
            <p>What is one specific way I will elevate someone else tomorrow?</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cp-remember">
          <span class="cp-remember-label">Remember</span>
          Humility is not thinking less of yourself, it's thinking of yourself less.
        </div>
        <div class="cp-scripture">"Count others more significant." — Phil. 2:3</div>
      </article>

      <article class="cp-card" id="trait-self-controlled">
        <div class="cp-card-top">
          <h2 class="cp-trait">Self-Controlled</h2>
          <p class="cp-descriptors">Disciplined · Patient · Measured</p>
          <div class="cp-framework-name">The Impulse Autopsy</div>
        </div>
        <p class="cp-recall">Recall a moment you acted on impulse or reacted too quickly.</p>
        <div class="cp-steps">
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Trace</span>
            <p>What was the trigger? What emotion drove the impulse? What is that emotion trying to tell me?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Pause</span>
            <p>What would a 10-second pause have revealed after the trigger appeared? How does giving in today quietly shape the outcomes I experience tomorrow?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Prepare</span>
            <p>What specific if-then plan will I commit to when this trigger arises in the future? What boundary can I set before this happens again?</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cp-remember">
          <span class="cp-remember-label">Remember</span>
          Self-control is caring more about the person you're becoming than the comfort you're craving.
        </div>
        <div class="cp-scripture">"Fruit of the Spirit is self-control." — Gal. 5:22</div>
      </article>

      <article class="cp-card" id="trait-hopeful">
        <div class="cp-card-top">
          <h2 class="cp-trait">Hopeful</h2>
          <p class="cp-descriptors">Optimistic · Resilient · Eager</p>
          <div class="cp-framework-name">The Redemption Lens</div>
        </div>
        <p class="cp-recall">Recall a disappointment or fear that lingered beyond the moment itself.</p>
        <div class="cp-steps">
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Acknowledge</span>
            <p>Where am I feeling stuck, and what is despair telling me here? How permanent does this feel on a 0–10 scale?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Recover</span>
            <p>What past difficulty have I navigated, and what resources (skills, knowledge, people) do I have now?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Project</span>
            <p>What is one possible future outcome I haven't considered? Between where I am and where I want to be, what is the next right thing to hope for or do?</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cp-remember">
          <span class="cp-remember-label">Remember</span>
          Hope is refusing to confuse today's pain with tomorrow's truth.
        </div>
        <div class="cp-scripture">"His mercies are new every morning." — Lam. 3:23</div>
      </article>

      <article class="cp-card" id="trait-wise">
        <div class="cp-card-top">
          <h2 class="cp-trait">Wise</h2>
          <p class="cp-descriptors">Discerning · Prudent · Understanding</p>
          <div class="cp-framework-name">The Decision Dissection</div>
        </div>
        <p class="cp-recall">Recall a decision you made today (or avoided) where wisdom was required.</p>
        <div class="cp-steps">
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Observe</span>
            <p>What facts did I actually have? What assumptions did I add? What emotions were influencing my judgment?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Consult</span>
            <p>Who has perspective or experience in this area? What would they likely say about this situation?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Extract</span>
            <p>What are the second- and third-order effects of this decision? What alternative exists beyond the options I am (or was) considering?</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cp-remember">
          <span class="cp-remember-label">Remember</span>
          Wisdom is loving the right things in the right order.
        </div>
        <div class="cp-scripture">"If any lacks wisdom, let him ask God." — Jas. 1:5</div>
      </article>

      <article class="cp-card" id="trait-joyful">
        <div class="cp-card-top">
          <h2 class="cp-trait">Joyful</h2>
          <p class="cp-descriptors">Grateful · Present · Light-hearted</p>
          <div class="cp-framework-name">The Joy Reframe</div>
        </div>
        <p class="cp-recall">Recall a moment today where joy felt absent, fragile, or easily lost.</p>
        <div class="cp-steps">
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Notice</span>
            <p>Where did my attention drift toward complaint, scarcity, or irritation? What story was I telling myself that diminished joy?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Reframe</span>
            <p>What did I overlook that was good? What alternative, truer story could I hold instead?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Embody</span>
            <p>What is one concrete way I can choose joy, be present, or express gratitude in the next 24 hours?</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cp-remember">
          <span class="cp-remember-label">Remember</span>
          Joy is not having the best of everything, but making the best of everything.
        </div>
        <div class="cp-scripture">"Rejoice in the Lord always." — Phil. 4:4</div>
      </article>

      <article class="cp-card" id="trait-peaceful">
        <div class="cp-card-top">
          <h2 class="cp-trait">Peaceful</h2>
          <p class="cp-descriptors">Calm · Slow to Anger · Gentle</p>
          <div class="cp-framework-name">The Inner Weather Report</div>
        </div>
        <p class="cp-recall">Recall a moment today where you felt anxious, tense, reactive, or internally unsettled.</p>
        <div class="cp-steps">
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Name</span>
            <p>What situation triggered the unrest? What was happening in my body (tight chest, shallow breath, racing thoughts)?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Investigate</span>
            <p>What is objectively true in this situation, and what interpretations, predictions, or catastrophes did I add?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Exhale</span>
            <p>Which thoughts are helping me respond wisely, and which are fueling unnecessary distress? Breathe in slowly; as you breathe out, consciously set down the latter and the tension they carry.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cp-remember">
          <span class="cp-remember-label">Remember</span>
          Peace is regulating your body so your mind can see clearly.
        </div>
        <div class="cp-scripture">"Perfect peace whose mind is stayed on you." — Isa. 26:3</div>
      </article>

      <article class="cp-card" id="trait-courageous">
        <div class="cp-card-top">
          <h2 class="cp-trait">Courageous</h2>
          <p class="cp-descriptors">Honest · Brave · Adventurous</p>
          <div class="cp-framework-name">The Discipline of Bravery</div>
        </div>
        <p class="cp-recall">Recall a moment today where you withheld something true, kind, or needed.</p>
        <div class="cp-steps">
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Surface</span>
            <p>Identify the specific fear present (rejection, conflict, failure, vulnerability, loss of control). What is the worst realistic outcome?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Weigh</span>
            <p>What is the cost of staying comfortable? What is the cost of acting with courage?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cp-step">
            <span class="cp-step-label">Commit</span>
            <p>What is one step—however small—I can take tomorrow to move toward what I've been avoiding? Choose the action and schedule it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cp-remember">
          <span class="cp-remember-label">Remember</span>
          Courage is not the absence of fear but the realization that something else matters more.
        </div>
        <div class="cp-scripture">"Be strong and courageous." — Deut. 31:6</div>
      </article>

    </div><!-- /.cp-grid -->

    <div class="cp-ai-prompt">
      <span class="cp-ai-label">AI Prompt</span>
      <p>Guide me through the framework for [INSERT TRAIT] one section at a time. Analyze my answers—if I'm being surface-level or letting myself off easy, push back and ask follow-up questions. Don't move on until we've gone deep. End by helping me apply the specific scripture and core truth to my situation.</p>
    </div>

  </div><!-- /.cp-page -->
</BaseLayout>

<style>
/* ── Page wrapper ─────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.cp-page {
  max-width: 1040px;
  padding-top: 2rem;
}

/* ── Subtitle ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.cp-subtitle {
  font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  font-style: italic;
  color: #7a7368;
  margin: 0 0 1.75rem;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

/* ── Card grid ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.cp-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  gap: 1.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
}

/* ── Individual card ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
.cp-card {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
  border: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.45);
  border-left: 3px solid #c2a86d;
  border-radius: 6px;
  overflow: hidden;
  transition: box-shadow 0.2s;
}

.cp-card:hover {
  box-shadow: 0 5px 22px rgba(70, 61, 52, 0.1);
}

/* ── Card header ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.cp-card-top {
  padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem 1rem;
  background: rgba(183, 156, 92, 0.07);
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(183, 156, 92, 0.15);
}

.cp-trait {
  font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
  font-size: 1.35rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #3d3830;
  margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.cp-descriptors {
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.7rem;
  color: #9e8c78;
  margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.01em;
}

.cp-framework-name {
  display: inline-block;
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.58rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.18em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: #b79c5c;
  background: rgba(183, 156, 92, 0.13);
  border: 1px solid rgba(183, 156, 92, 0.3);
  padding: 0.22rem 0.65rem;
  border-radius: 2px;
}

/* ── Recall prompt ────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.cp-recall {
  font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 0.93rem;
  color: #5e554b;
  line-height: 1.65;
  font-style: italic;
  padding: 0.85rem 1.25rem;
  background: rgba(233, 227, 216, 0.4);
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.3);
  margin: 0;
}

.cp-recall::before {
  content: 'Recall';
  display: block;
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.56rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  font-style: normal;
  letter-spacing: 0.18em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: #b79c5c;
  margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
}

/* ── Steps ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.cp-steps {
  padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0;
  flex: 1;
}

.cp-step {
  padding: 0.7rem 0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.25);
}

.cp-step:first-child {
  padding-top: 0;
}

.cp-step:last-child {
  border-bottom: none;
  padding-bottom: 0;
}

.cp-step-label {
  display: block;
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.58rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.16em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: #b79c5c;
  margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
}

.cp-step p {
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  color: #5e554b;
  line-height: 1.65;
  margin: 0;
}

/* ── Remember block ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
.cp-remember {
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  color: #4f4a44;
  line-height: 1.6;
  background: rgba(183, 156, 92, 0.07);
  border-top: 1px solid rgba(183, 156, 92, 0.18);
  padding: 0.75rem 1.1rem;
  margin-top: auto;
}

.cp-remember-label {
  display: block;
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.56rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.18em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: #b79c5c;
  margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
}

/* ── Scripture footer ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
.cp-scripture {
  font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  font-style: italic;
  color: #9e8c78;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 0.7rem 1.25rem 0.8rem;
  border-top: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.35);
  background: rgba(70, 61, 52, 0.02);
}

/* ── AI Prompt ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
.cp-ai-prompt {
  background: rgba(70, 61, 52, 0.04);
  border: 1px solid rgba(199, 187, 170, 0.45);
  border-radius: 6px;
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: 1rem;
}

.cp-ai-label {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.58rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.18em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: #f3efe9;
  background: #6a6156;
  padding: 0.3rem 0.65rem;
  border-radius: 2px;
  margin-top: 0.1rem;
}

.cp-ai-prompt p {
  font-family: 'EB Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 0.93rem;
  color: #5e554b;
  line-height: 1.75;
  margin: 0;
}

/* ── Responsive: tablet → 1 column ───────────────────────────── */
@media (max-width: 720px) {
  .cp-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }

  .cp-ai-prompt {
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }
}

/* ── Responsive: mobile refinements ──────────────────────────── */
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .cp-trait {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  .cp-card-top {
    padding: 0.9rem 1rem 0.85rem;
  }

  .cp-recall,
  .cp-steps {
    padding-left: 1rem;
    padding-right: 1rem;
  }

  .cp-remember {
    padding-left: 1rem;
    padding-right: 1rem;
  }
}
</style>
